* text eol=lf

*.jar binary

*.exe binary

*scripts/zipalgo_mac binary

*scripts/zipalgo_linux binary

# Compiled/binary artifacts — MUST be excluded from the `* text eol=lf` rule
# above, which otherwise runs CRLF->LF normalization on them. That rule is
# exactly what corrupted sim/terminal_sim.pyd (a CRLF byte pair inside the DLL
# was collapsed, shrinking it by 1 byte and breaking the PE header offsets —
# every historical blob of it is dead; rebuild + recommit from source).
*.pyd binary
*.so binary
*.dll binary
*.bin binary
*.pt binary
*.whl binary
scripts/test_algo_* binary

# Fidelity-gate corpus: the pod's setup_runpod.sh gate must diff replays that
# are BYTE-IDENTICAL to the ones validated locally. Some carry CRLF line
# endings; both parsers (replay.rs, replay_utils.py) handle either, but the
# gate inputs must never be rewritten in transit.
*.replay -text

